The future King lashes out at "people like Burrell" and rails against vengeful Royal staff in the handwritten note from November 2002. But the Old Bailey case collapsed after the Queen recalled he told her he was keeping some of Diana's things. The court heard Prince Charles had teams of servants, including one to squeeze his toothpaste. In his letter to Majorie Dawson, who was Princess Alexandra's maid, Charles writes: "I find it utterly incredible, as I have done nothing but show people like Paul Burrell every consideration over the years.